
Step 1: Identify unused parameters in methods/constructors.

Step 2: If the method is private and only called within its own class:

Remove the parameter
Update all call sites accordingly
Step 3: If it's part of a public API (public/protected/interface implementation):

Keep the parameter (for backward compatibility)
Optionally add // Unused parameter or @SuppressWarnings("unused")
Note: Automatic refactoring should only remove parameters from private methods
